# **1ï¸âƒ£ On-Premises (Traditional Infrastructure)**

ğŸ“Œ Definition:- 
    All IT resources are hosted **inside your organizationâ€™s data center**. You own and manage all hardware, storage, networking, and servers.

ğŸ“Œ Key Characteristics:-

* Full control over physical infrastructure
* Requires in-house IT team
* High capital expenditure (CapEx)
* Slow to scale; needs hardware procurement
* Security entirely managed internally

ğŸ“Œ AWS Equivalent Services (for comparison):-
* **AWS Outposts** â†’ Brings AWS hardware/services on-prem
* **VMware Cloud on AWS** â†’ Run your VMware workloads on AWS
* **Storage Gateway** â†’ Connect on-prem storage with AWS

ğŸ“Œ Pros:-
* Maximum control & compliance
* Can meet strict government or financial regulations
