# **2ï¸âƒ£ AWS Cloud (Public Cloud)**
ğŸ“Œ Definition:- 
     AWS hosts your IT resources (compute, storage, network, databases, etc.) in **its global data centers**. You pay only for what you use (OpEx model).

ğŸ“Œ Core AWS Services:-

| Category   | Services                       | Notes                                       |
| ---------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |
| Compute    | EC2, Lambda, Elastic Beanstalk | EC2 â†’ virtual servers, Lambda â†’ serverless  |
| Storage    | S3, EBS, EFS, Glacier          | Object, block, file storage                 |
| Database   | RDS, DynamoDB, Aurora          | Managed relational & NoSQL databases        |
| Networking | VPC, Route53, Direct Connect   | Secure networking, DNS, hybrid connectivity |
| Security   | IAM, KMS, GuardDuty            | Identity, key management, threat detection  |
| Monitoring | CloudWatch, CloudTrail         | Logs, metrics, auditing                     |

ğŸ“Œ Pros:-
* Scalable & flexible (auto-scaling, load balancers)
* Fast provisioning (minutes vs weeks)
* Low upfront cost (pay-as-you-go)
* Global reach with multiple regions & availability zones
* Managed services reduce operational load

ğŸ“Œ Cons:-
* Ongoing OpEx cost
* Requires internet connectivity
* Vendor lock-in risk

ğŸ“Œ Best For:-
* Startups & SMEs
* Fast-scaling apps (e-commerce, SaaS, fintech)
* AI/ML workloads
* Disaster recovery & backup

---

# **3ï¸âƒ£ Hybrid Cloud (AWS + On-Prem)**

ğŸ“Œ Definition:-
    A combination of your **on-premises data center** + **AWS Cloud**. Some workloads run locally, while others run on AWS for scalability, DR, or cloud migration.

ğŸ“Œ AWS Services Supporting Hybrid:-

| Service             | Purpose                                          |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| AWS Outposts        | Run AWS hardware & services on-prem              |
| AWS Direct Connect  | Dedicated network connection from on-prem to AWS |
| Storage Gateway     | Connect on-prem storage to AWS cloud             |
| VMware Cloud on AWS | Run VMware workloads in AWS environment          |
| AWS Backup          | Centralized backup for on-prem + cloud           |

ğŸ“Œ Pros:-
* Flexible: keep sensitive data on-prem, scale in cloud
* Smooth migration to cloud
* Disaster recovery with cloud
* High availability

ğŸ“Œ Cons:-
* Complex setup & management
* Skilled IT staff required
* Cost of both on-prem + cloud

ğŸ“Œ Best For:-
* Large enterprises with legacy apps
* Companies migrating gradually to AWS
* Regulated industries (healthcare, banking)
* Disaster recovery and backup solutions

---

# **ğŸ“Š AWS Cloud Models Comparison Table**

| Feature             | On-Premises         | AWS Cloud             | Hybrid (AWS + On-Prem)        |
| ------------------- | ------------------- | --------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| **Cost Model**      | CapEx               | Pay-as-you-go (OpEx)  | Mixed CapEx + OpEx            |
| **Control**         | Maximum             | Limited               | Moderate                      |
| **Scalability**     | Slow                | Fast (auto-scaling)   | Medium                        |
| **Security**        | Fully in-house      | Shared responsibility | Strong but complex            |
| **Deployment Time** | Weeks to months     | Minutes to hours      | Medium                        |
| **Maintenance**     | Company             | AWS managed           | Both                          |
| **Best Use Cases**  | Government, Banking | Startups, SMEs        | Large enterprises, migration  |
| **Examples**        | Private datacenter  | EC2, S3, RDS, Lambda  | AWS Outposts, Storage Gateway |

